# Approved build commands
approved_commands := {
    ["go", "build", "-o", "app"],
    ["go", "build", "-o=app", "."],
    ["make", "all"],
    ["npm", "run", "build"]
}

deny contains msg if {
    not input.cmd in approved_commands
    msg := sprintf("Unauthorized build command: %v", [input.cmd])
}
```

**Usage in Policy:**
Add this to your policy document:

```json
{
  "steps": {
    "build": {
      "attestations": [
        {
          "type": "https://witness.dev/attestations/command-run/v0.1",
          "regopolicies": [
            {
              "name": "commandrun_command_allowlist",
              "module": "<base64-encoded-rego>"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

This Rego policy has been verified to work with actual command-run attestations.

